254
00:13:22,910 --> 00:13:24,605
are too uncomfortable
to listen to now.

255
00:13:24,679 --> 00:13:26,010
I'm calling next time.
Fine.

256
00:13:26,381 --> 00:13:28,611
Look, if we're going to
accomplish anything in this town,

257
00:13:28,683 --> 00:13:29,843
we are gonna
need wheels.

258
00:13:33,421 --> 00:13:36,254
Shawn, we have reached
a new low point in our life.

259
00:13:36,324 --> 00:13:38,087
<i>Are you kidding me?
It's like Driving Miss Daisy.</i>

260
00:13:38,159 --> 00:13:39,786
Except you
get to be Miss Daisy.

261
00:13:39,804 --> 00:13:42,238
I don't wanna be
in the movie, Shawn.

262
00:13:43,608 --> 00:13:46,099
Looks like the doctor
stays pretty busy.

263
00:13:48,846 --> 00:13:51,815
Guess you're out of luck
if you need a massage.

264
00:13:54,852 --> 00:13:57,320
Good job saving
your receipts, Patrick.

265
00:14:00,058 --> 00:14:01,548
May I help you, gentlemen?

266
00:14:01,626 --> 00:14:03,093
Hello, Doc Gooden.

267
00:14:03,161 --> 00:14:04,492
My partner,
plus too much

268
00:14:04,562 --> 00:14:06,553
cinnamon monkey bread
equals tummy shame.

269
00:14:06,631 --> 00:14:08,121
Can you help us?

270
00:14:08,232 --> 00:14:10,097
I'll see him
after my next patient.

271
00:14:16,107 --> 00:14:17,938
Doc, this could
get ugly fast.

272
00:14:18,976 --> 00:14:20,034
All right.

273
00:14:31,422 --> 00:14:32,719
Sheriff Jackson
mentioned we had

274
00:14:32,790 --> 00:14:35,054
a couple of visitors
in town today.

275
00:14:35,126 --> 00:14:38,254
You are aware the cinnamon
festival has been cancelled.

276
00:14:38,329 --> 00:14:39,796
Oh, yes.

277
00:14:39,864 --> 00:14:42,332
We heard there was
some sort of tragedy.

278
00:14:42,399 --> 00:14:44,196
Must be so difficult

279
00:14:44,268 --> 00:14:47,260
in a small, happy town
like Dual Spires.

280
00:14:48,206 --> 00:14:50,436
Put this on and then lay
face down on my table.

281
00:14:50,675 --> 00:14:53,041
Uh, well you know...
Ah, ahh!

282
00:14:53,344 --> 00:14:54,368
Actually, I think...

283
00:14:54,445 --> 00:14:55,434
Snap to it.

284
00:14:56,247 --> 00:14:57,680
I'm not putting this on.

285
00:14:59,984 --> 00:15:00,973
Fine.

286
00:15:01,919 --> 00:15:05,150
So how well did you
know the girl?

287
00:15:06,824 --> 00:15:08,815
I'm sorry, I don't
know why I do that.

288
00:15:08,893 --> 00:15:11,953
I can just sense that
you have a heavy heart.

289
00:15:13,197 --> 00:15:15,028
I'm a woman of science.

290
00:15:15,099 --> 00:15:16,157
And law.

291
00:15:16,234 --> 00:15:17,223
And accounting.

292
00:15:17,835 --> 00:15:19,564
But that doesn't mean
that I don't feel.

293
00:15:21,005 --> 00:15:23,166
Paula was
a troubled young girl.

294
00:15:23,407 --> 00:15:25,841
I wish I could have
done more to help her.

295
00:15:25,910 --> 00:15:27,002
You were her
psychiatrist?

296
00:15:28,346 --> 00:15:29,836
You ask a lot of questions.

297
00:15:29,914 --> 00:15:32,474
It's just... I recently
lost someone myself.

298
00:15:33,451 --> 00:15:35,419
He was murdered too,
so I know how difficult...

299
00:15:35,485 --> 00:15:37,612
Paula wasn't murdered.
Who told you that?

300
00:15:37,755 --> 00:15:39,120
Oh, no one.

301
00:15:39,524 --> 00:15:41,014
I just assumed, because...

302
00:15:43,327 --> 00:15:45,557
I haven't done
an autopsy yet.

303
00:15:52,937 --> 00:15:55,235
There are no obvious signs
of foul play.

304
00:15:57,375 --> 00:15:59,002
I'm sorry,
I didn't mean to...

305
00:15:59,577 --> 00:16:02,102
No, it's not you.

306
00:16:02,446 --> 00:16:04,573
Like I said, she was
a troubled young girl.

307
00:16:04,649 --> 00:16:06,082
She had a dangerous side.

308
00:16:07,518 --> 00:16:09,110
Nothing scared her.

309
00:16:09,187 --> 00:16:10,279
Not even dying.

310
00:16:10,988 --> 00:16:12,455
You think she
may have taken her own...

311
00:16:12,523 --> 00:16:15,014
No, I can't bear
that thought.

312
00:16:15,226 --> 00:16:17,387
I've said too
much to a stranger.

313
00:16:17,528 --> 00:16:19,018
I should be ashamed.

314
00:16:20,064 --> 00:16:21,224
For caring?

315
00:16:23,334 --> 00:16:24,596
No, you shouldn't.

316
00:16:27,474 --> 00:16:29,772
You know, I actually
feel better.

317
00:16:29,943 --> 00:16:31,706
The myna bird
can come in now.

318
00:16:33,406 --> 00:16:34,498
What's up next?

319
00:16:34,574 --> 00:16:36,064
We need to find
our cinnamon king.

320
00:16:36,142 --> 00:16:37,234
That kid
has a secret.

321
00:16:37,310 --> 00:16:38,709
What did
grandma tell you

322
00:16:38,778 --> 00:16:40,507
about wandering off
in the store?

323
00:16:43,450 --> 00:16:44,610
Oh, come on.

324
00:16:46,353 --> 00:16:47,377
I was getting
ready to say...

325
00:16:47,454 --> 00:16:48,751
That would have
been too much.

326
00:16:51,018 --> 00:16:52,485
Dude. That's him.

327
00:16:53,594 --> 00:16:55,118
Dude, that's our guy.

328
00:17:36,377 --> 00:17:38,242
Oh, Sheriff.

329
00:17:38,313 --> 00:17:39,541
Didn't expect
to see you here.

330
00:17:40,248 --> 00:17:41,840
I live here.
What do you mean?

331
00:17:42,417 --> 00:17:44,214
Of course you do.
Oh...

332
00:17:44,285 --> 00:17:46,219
You're Randy's father.

333
00:17:46,287 --> 00:17:47,686
Yes, wow.

334
00:17:48,123 --> 00:17:51,388
You guys have Bob Barker, Doc
Gooden, and Randy Jackson.

335
00:17:51,459 --> 00:17:53,086
All living in
the same inlet town

336
00:17:53,161 --> 00:17:54,719
with no cars, cell
phones, or internet.

337
00:17:54,796 --> 00:17:56,559
Shawn, we need to pitch
this to Mark Burnett.

338
00:17:56,631 --> 00:17:59,327
You fellas realize
the festival is canceled.

339
00:17:59,634 --> 00:18:03,035
As you know, we lost someone
very dear to us today.

340
00:18:03,104 --> 00:18:04,935
That's actually why
we dropped by, Sheriff.

341
00:18:05,006 --> 00:18:07,975
You see, Gus and I are grief
counselors back in the big city.

342
00:18:08,042 --> 00:18:10,408
And you all have been
so kind and welcoming to us

343
00:18:10,478 --> 00:18:11,740
that we figured
the least we could do

344
00:18:11,813 --> 00:18:14,213
would be to offer our
services before we left town.

345
00:18:14,282 --> 00:18:15,476
Well, come on in, fellas.

346
00:18:16,851 --> 00:18:17,943
Yeah.

347
00:18:21,790 --> 00:18:24,657
I'll confess, Randy and I
haven't been communicating

348
00:18:24,726 --> 00:18:26,216
too well as of late.

349
00:18:27,796 --> 00:18:30,765
I know he's hurting,
but he won't talk to me.

350
00:18:33,902 --> 00:18:35,301
You know,
it wasn't too long ago

351
00:18:35,370 --> 00:18:37,099
that Gus and I
were Randy's age.

352
00:18:37,172 --> 00:18:38,469
It was a pretty
long time ago.

353
00:18:38,540 --> 00:18:39,564
Ah, it wasn't
that long ago.

354
00:18:39,641 --> 00:18:40,630
You like to think so.

355
00:18:40,708 --> 00:18:42,369
I can't do this with you right now.
Fine.

356
00:18:43,077 --> 00:18:44,601
He's upstairs
in his room.

357
00:18:44,679 --> 00:18:45,907
We'll give it a shot.

358
00:18:54,289 --> 00:18:56,723
So my dad hired you
to shake me down, right?

359
00:18:57,225 --> 00:18:58,954
I'm fine.
I barely knew Paula.

360
00:19:00,094 --> 00:19:02,858
Then why did the two of you share
secret, special lover earrings?

361
00:19:03,631 --> 00:19:06,828
Come on, Randy.
How long had you been seeing her?

362
00:19:06,901 --> 00:19:08,027
Who are you?

363
00:19:08,436 --> 00:19:10,233
A couple of guys with a
passion for the truth.

364
00:19:10,305 --> 00:19:11,567
And cinnamon.

365
00:19:13,341 --> 00:19:15,104
We'd been together
six months.

366
00:19:16,177 --> 00:19:17,576
Why was it a secret?

367
00:19:17,645 --> 00:19:18,907
It's complicated.

368
00:19:19,180 --> 00:19:22,308
<i>I get it. It's Pretty in Pink.
 You're Andrew McCarthy.</i>

369
00:19:23,151 --> 00:19:24,584
Who's Andrew McCarthy?

370
00:19:24,652 --> 00:19:25,676
That's fair.

371
00:19:25,753 --> 00:19:27,243
Where were you
the night Paula died?

372
00:19:27,455 --> 00:19:29,082
I was at the library,
studying.

373
00:19:29,157 --> 00:19:30,488
The librarian
can confirm it.

374
00:19:30,558 --> 00:19:32,321
Do you always study
so late on a Friday?

375
00:19:32,427 --> 00:19:34,588
I'm at the library
almost every night.

376
00:19:34,662 --> 00:19:36,289
I've been taking
correspondence courses.

377
00:19:36,364 --> 00:19:37,922
I need a business degree
to be a good leader.

378
00:19:38,433 --> 00:19:39,491
That's true.

379
00:19:42,704 --> 00:19:44,001
I never could
have hurt her.

380
00:19:50,278 --> 00:19:51,575
I loved Paula.

381
00:19:54,282 --> 00:19:56,147
We were gonna see
the world together.

382
00:19:56,851 --> 00:19:58,716
I'm gonna be so
lost without her.

383
00:20:01,422 --> 00:20:02,753
Oh, Paula.

384
00:20:04,993 --> 00:20:06,153
Paula.

385
00:20:09,130 --> 00:20:10,290
Paula.

386
00:20:12,333 --> 00:20:13,357
Paula.

387
00:20:16,371 --> 00:20:17,360
Paula.

388
00:20:17,872 --> 00:20:19,134
That's a little
dramatic, don't you...

389
00:20:21,910 --> 00:20:23,275
You have a problem.

390
00:20:39,260 --> 00:20:40,249
Excuse us.

391
00:20:41,729 --> 00:20:43,697
Keep your
voice down, please.

392
00:20:44,565 --> 00:20:46,328
It's just us
and you.

393
00:20:46,401 --> 00:20:49,234
Just a bunch of words on
paper to you guys, right?

394
00:20:49,304 --> 00:20:50,532
Wrong.

395
00:20:50,605 --> 00:20:53,733
Each is alive
with a story to tell.

396
00:20:54,208 --> 00:20:55,402
Listen.

397
00:20:58,746 --> 00:21:01,271
I'm just
messing with you guys.

398
00:21:02,617 --> 00:21:05,211
Thanks for playing along.
That's really sweet.

399
00:21:05,653 --> 00:21:07,450
I'm Maudette Hornsby.

400
00:21:08,623 --> 00:21:10,181
Isn't cherry the best?

401
00:21:11,659 --> 00:21:12,751
The best what?

402
00:21:13,628 --> 00:21:14,959
Everything, silly.

403
00:21:16,130 --> 00:21:17,392
I thought you were psychic.

404
00:21:17,465 --> 00:21:19,092
I am.
I'm the psychic.

405
00:21:19,167 --> 00:21:20,634
But how did
you know that?

406
00:21:20,702 --> 00:21:22,135
Mmm, word travels.

407
00:21:22,203 --> 00:21:24,467
You know, we don't get a
lot of gossip around here.

408
00:21:24,539 --> 00:21:27,372
So untimely death,
a psychic,

409
00:21:27,442 --> 00:21:29,034
and a black man,
all in one day.

410
00:21:29,444 --> 00:21:30,468
Epic.

411
00:21:30,545 --> 00:21:32,513
I really thought we
were being discreet.

412
00:21:32,580 --> 00:21:34,070
Do you even know
what discreet is?

413
00:21:34,515 --> 00:21:35,675
That's a
serious question.

414
00:21:35,750 --> 00:21:37,081
I know what...
Shh!

415
00:21:38,386 --> 00:21:40,320
Was Randy Jackson with you
the night Paula died?

416
00:21:40,388 --> 00:21:41,377
Why?

417
00:21:41,456 --> 00:21:44,186
Do you think she was
M- U-R-D-E-R-E-D or something?

418
00:21:44,258 --> 00:21:45,589
M- A-Y-B-E.

419
00:21:46,961 --> 00:21:48,394
Yes, Randy was here.

420
00:21:49,097 --> 00:21:52,624
We have a very
special bond, you see.

421
00:21:53,401 --> 00:21:55,392
His mom passed away
when he was very young.

422
00:21:55,470 --> 00:21:57,097
Sheriff Jackson
never remarried.

423
00:21:57,171 --> 00:22:01,733
So I sort of stepped
in and filled a role.

424
00:22:02,510 --> 00:22:03,704
For both of them.

425
00:22:10,551 --> 00:22:12,712
Is there anything else
you need to know?

426
00:22:12,787 --> 00:22:13,845
Uh...

427
00:22:14,322 --> 00:22:15,789
Feels pretty good
for now.

428
00:22:15,857 --> 00:22:17,085
Do you mind
if we poke around?

429
00:22:17,158 --> 00:22:18,147
Poke?
Peek.

430
00:22:18,226 --> 00:22:19,250
Peek.
Peek around.

431
00:22:19,327 --> 00:22:20,316
Yes.

432
00:22:21,195 --> 00:22:22,457
Knock yourselves out.

433
00:22:23,131 --> 00:22:25,361
Okay, remember
the last email,

434
00:22:25,533 --> 00:22:26,932
the one with all
the weird hieroglyphics?

435
00:22:27,035 --> 00:22:28,161
They were letters
and numbers, Shawn.

436
00:22:28,236 --> 00:22:29,533
Okay, it was one
of these things.

437
00:22:29,604 --> 00:22:30,969
The Dewey
Decimal System?

438
00:22:31,039 --> 00:22:32,336
I didn't even know
they still used this.

439
00:22:32,407 --> 00:22:33,965
That's 'cause people don't
want to crack war codes

440
00:22:34,042 --> 00:22:35,066
<i>when the payoff
is Jane Eyre.</i>

441
00:22:35,143 --> 00:22:36,132
What was the
number, Shawn?

442
00:22:36,210 --> 00:22:38,804
F-7-9-6-dot-3-5-2.

443
00:22:38,880 --> 00:22:41,110
Seven hundred's that's
sports and recreation.

444
00:22:49,057 --> 00:22:50,922
These books
are archaic.

445
00:22:50,992 --> 00:22:52,186
And really old.

446
00:22:53,928 --> 00:22:55,395
Except this one.

447
00:22:58,366 --> 00:22:59,697
By Earl Wyndam.

448
00:22:59,767 --> 00:23:01,598
My short game
could use some work.

449
00:23:03,538 --> 00:23:04,869
There's no pictures?

450
00:23:05,473 --> 00:23:07,805
This is the weirdest
golf book I've ever seen.

451
00:23:07,875 --> 00:23:08,967
Let me see that.

452
00:23:12,346 --> 00:23:15,281
Our emailer wants us to think
that Paula was reincarnated?

453
00:23:15,349 --> 00:23:16,475
We should get
back to the lake.

454
00:23:16,551 --> 00:23:18,178
Juliet should have
something by now.

455
00:23:20,688 --> 00:23:22,053
You're gonna need
a library card

456
00:23:22,123 --> 00:23:23,556
if you want to check
something out.

457
00:23:24,892 --> 00:23:26,655
I think we're good,
Maudette.

458
00:23:31,966 --> 00:23:33,593
Juliet, it's Gus.

459
00:23:34,936 --> 00:23:37,166
Gus, what's going on?
Is Shawn okay?

460
00:23:37,238 --> 00:23:38,830
Oh, he's fine.
Tell her I said "Hi."

461
00:23:39,140 --> 00:23:40,505
Ask her what
she's wearing.

462
00:23:40,575 --> 00:23:42,008
Do you have anything
on Paula Merral?

463
00:23:42,376 --> 00:23:43,365
Do I?

464
00:23:43,444 --> 00:23:44,934
Look, I don't know
what you guys

465
00:23:45,012 --> 00:23:46,240
have gotten yourselves
into up there,

466
00:23:46,314 --> 00:23:48,908
but Paula Merral drowned
here seven years ago.

467
00:23:51,419 --> 00:23:52,545
What?

468
00:23:52,620 --> 00:23:53,746
Did she say "Hi" back?

469
00:24:06,210 --> 00:24:07,575
Is he looking at us?

470
00:24:07,945 --> 00:24:08,969
I think he is.

471
00:24:12,316 --> 00:24:14,113
Dude, take it easy.
That's your seventh piece.

472
00:24:14,185 --> 00:24:16,016
You know I get hungry
when I get freaked out.

473
00:24:16,087 --> 00:24:17,418
Besides, you've had five.

474
00:24:17,488 --> 00:24:19,149
Exactly, I believe
in portion control.

475
00:24:19,223 --> 00:24:20,747
A girl drowns,
gets reincarnated,

476
00:24:20,825 --> 00:24:22,349
and drowns again
seven years later?

477
00:24:22,426 --> 00:24:23,484
Worst cinnamon festival ever.

478
00:24:27,098 --> 00:24:28,588
We definitely
stick out around here.

479
00:24:28,766 --> 00:24:30,631
True, but not
as bad as them.

480
00:24:35,039 --> 00:24:36,563
What are you
staring at, Jesup?

481
00:24:38,075 --> 00:24:39,133
Scoot.

482
00:24:39,543 --> 00:24:42,706
Wow, did you guys just
hoof it from the highway?

483
00:24:42,780 --> 00:24:44,372
What? Oh, hell no.

484
00:24:44,448 --> 00:24:46,109
No, we took the seven-mile
dirt road that connects

485
00:24:46,183 --> 00:24:47,946
this crap hole
to the next town over.

486
00:24:48,019 --> 00:24:49,486
We came up here because
the chief wanted us

487
00:24:49,553 --> 00:24:51,453
to get a positive ID
on Paula Merral's body.

488
00:24:51,522 --> 00:24:53,353
To see if it matched the one
found in Santa Barbara?

489
00:24:53,424 --> 00:24:54,516
No, see
that's the thing.

490
00:24:54,592 --> 00:24:55,991
We never
recovered her body.

491
00:24:56,060 --> 00:24:57,493
Which didn't
sit well with me.

492
00:24:57,862 --> 00:25:00,262
The inlet where she supposedly
drowned has no current,

493
00:25:00,331 --> 00:25:01,992
which means her body
should have floated up

494
00:25:02,066 --> 00:25:04,193
between 2.3 to 3.1 days.

495
00:25:05,603 --> 00:25:06,934
Oh, I know this because
waiting for corpses

496
00:25:07,004 --> 00:25:08,494
to resurface is
a passion in my life.

497
00:25:08,706 --> 00:25:10,970
The sweater she was wearing
was found on the shoreline.

498
00:25:11,042 --> 00:25:13,476
And her bike was discovered
at the end of a nearby dock.

499
00:25:13,544 --> 00:25:15,739
It was lying next to a
pile of sunflower seeds,

500
00:25:15,813 --> 00:25:17,007
which was also weird.

501
00:25:17,081 --> 00:25:19,549
What 11-year-old girl
chews sunflower seeds?

502
00:25:24,221 --> 00:25:25,347
Excuse me, Flo.

503
00:25:25,656 --> 00:25:28,022
Where might we find the proprietors
of this fine establishment?

504
00:25:28,125 --> 00:25:29,524
Robert and Michelle?

505
00:25:29,760 --> 00:25:32,126
They've been home ever since
they got the news about Paula.

506
00:25:37,661 --> 00:25:39,788
Do you have something you
want to tell us, Mr. Barker?

507
00:25:43,700 --> 00:25:46,032
Twelve years ago,
Michelle's sister, Lucy

508
00:25:46,101 --> 00:25:47,363
ran away from Dual Spires,

509
00:25:47,436 --> 00:25:49,165
taking seven-year-old
Paula with her.

510
00:25:49,738 --> 00:25:51,296
We were worried
sick about Paula.

