00:36:27,249 --> 00:36:28,341
What did Paula do?

767
00:36:28,417 --> 00:36:29,714
She freaked out
and went on this rant

768
00:36:29,785 --> 00:36:30,911
about how I'm a hypocrite

769
00:36:30,986 --> 00:36:32,851
'cause I spend a lot of time
with my ex-girlfriend.

770
00:36:32,922 --> 00:36:34,014
And who's that?

771
00:36:35,624 --> 00:36:36,886
That's none of your business.

772
00:36:37,693 --> 00:36:39,524
What is it with all the secret
relationships in this town?

773
00:36:39,595 --> 00:36:41,062
<i>It's like
General Hospital.</i>

774
00:36:43,466 --> 00:36:44,990
You're kidding me.

775
00:36:45,067 --> 00:36:46,227
All right, that's it.

776
00:36:46,302 --> 00:36:48,327
Is there a film,
or a television series,

777
00:36:48,404 --> 00:36:49,928
that you people actually saw?

778
00:36:50,005 --> 00:36:51,870
The town gets together
every Thursday night

779
00:36:51,941 --> 00:36:53,203
<i>to watch
reruns of Everwood.</i>

780
00:36:53,509 --> 00:36:55,340
Okay, I can work with that.

781
00:36:55,411 --> 00:36:56,605
What happened next?

782
00:36:56,679 --> 00:36:58,840
She got mad at me
for hurting a blind person.

783
00:36:58,914 --> 00:37:00,381
She then went
to find help for Jack.

784
00:37:00,850 --> 00:37:01,908
I offered to go with her,

785
00:37:01,984 --> 00:37:03,952
but she wanted
nothing to do with me.

786
00:37:04,019 --> 00:37:05,577
So I tied his
shoelaces together,

787
00:37:05,654 --> 00:37:07,918
and went to the library
and waited to hear from her.

788
00:37:11,127 --> 00:37:13,095
Of course,

789
00:37:13,529 --> 00:37:14,518
I never did.

790
00:37:15,331 --> 00:37:17,959
<i>Just like Treat Williams'
character on Everwood.</i>

791
00:37:18,033 --> 00:37:19,364
Never got to say
good-bye to his wife.

792
00:37:19,435 --> 00:37:20,493
Shawn.

793
00:37:22,705 --> 00:37:25,538
Look, I'm telling
you guys the truth.

794
00:37:25,608 --> 00:37:27,439
Plus, I have an alibi,
remember?

795
00:37:28,644 --> 00:37:29,975
All right.

796
00:37:30,446 --> 00:37:32,311
But we're on
to you, Randy.

797
00:37:32,381 --> 00:37:34,542
Just like the townspeople of
Everwood were on to the fact

798
00:37:34,617 --> 00:37:35,879
that Nina was
a surrogate mother.

799
00:37:35,951 --> 00:37:37,782
Will you stop it?
Enough.

800
00:37:39,922 --> 00:37:40,911
She was.

801
00:37:41,357 --> 00:37:42,381
Thank you.

802
00:37:44,927 --> 00:37:46,952
So, who do we think
Randy's ex is?

803
00:37:47,229 --> 00:37:48,856
Mmm, Jules, you gotta
order a piece of this pie.

804
00:37:48,964 --> 00:37:51,159
I did. You guys
immediately ate it.

805
00:37:51,233 --> 00:37:54,100
Well, it's gotta be someone
who's into the creepsters,

806
00:37:54,170 --> 00:37:56,161
but I'm guessing she's older,
'cause I'm yet to see

807
00:37:56,238 --> 00:37:57,728
a woman under the
age of 35 in this town.

808
00:37:57,807 --> 00:37:59,798
It's also someone that Randy
spends consistent time with.

809
00:37:59,875 --> 00:38:01,399
Mmm-hmm, mmm-hmm.

810
00:38:04,513 --> 00:38:05,673
I'm getting something.

811
00:38:06,048 --> 00:38:07,515
I'm at the library
almost every night.

812
00:38:07,750 --> 00:38:10,378
Randy and I have a very
special bond, you see.

813
00:38:12,121 --> 00:38:13,782
Four slices to go, please.

814
00:38:14,924 --> 00:38:17,324
If Maudette was sleeping
with Randy, that's gross.

815
00:38:17,393 --> 00:38:18,655
She practically raised him.

816
00:38:18,727 --> 00:38:19,989
The only thing that
would make it grosser

817
00:38:20,062 --> 00:38:21,393
is if she wasn't attractive.

818
00:38:21,464 --> 00:38:22,954
What's wrong with you?

819
00:38:23,032 --> 00:38:25,933
This goes beyond Maudette
getting her Pamela Smart on.

820
00:38:26,001 --> 00:38:27,161
I think she killed Paula.

821
00:38:27,236 --> 00:38:28,362
What?
How do you figure?

822
00:38:28,437 --> 00:38:30,905
I'm sensing that Randy went
to the library that night

823
00:38:30,973 --> 00:38:32,270
to finally tell Maudette

824
00:38:32,341 --> 00:38:34,172
that he and Paula
were leaving Dual Spires.

825
00:38:34,477 --> 00:38:36,172
Sent her into
a jealous rage.

826
00:38:36,245 --> 00:38:38,270
She snuck out,
killed Paula,

827
00:38:38,347 --> 00:38:39,939
because if she
couldn't have Randy,

828
00:38:40,015 --> 00:38:41,380
no woman would.

829
00:38:41,450 --> 00:38:42,747
That changes everything.

830
00:38:43,953 --> 00:38:46,148
Remind me to never have
an affair with an older woman

831
00:38:46,222 --> 00:38:47,712
or a librarian.

832
00:38:47,790 --> 00:38:49,155
Maudette.

833
00:38:50,693 --> 00:38:52,320
That's not good.
Oh.

834
00:38:52,761 --> 00:38:54,524
I am so sick
of this town.

835
00:38:57,800 --> 00:38:59,791
Go ahead and wheel her around
the corner to my office.

836
00:39:11,347 --> 00:39:13,474
I can't believe
Maudette Hornsby

837
00:39:13,549 --> 00:39:15,380
was taking
advantage of my son.

838
00:39:16,685 --> 00:39:18,448
Taking advantage
is a little strong.

839
00:39:18,521 --> 00:39:20,250
The dude was 17
and she was fine.

840
00:39:21,490 --> 00:39:23,151
What exactly constitutes
the difference between

841
00:39:23,225 --> 00:39:25,420
altar boy Gus
and degenerate Gus?

842
00:39:25,494 --> 00:39:27,655
Reputation
was everything to Maudette.

843
00:39:27,730 --> 00:39:30,221
The prospect of the town
knowing about that scandal

844
00:39:30,299 --> 00:39:32,062
was probably more
than she could live with.

845
00:39:32,134 --> 00:39:34,227
I better speak to my boy.

846
00:39:34,303 --> 00:39:36,533
And I'll get on
that autopsy.

847
00:39:38,374 --> 00:39:39,432
The fact that
she murdered someone

848
00:39:39,508 --> 00:39:41,533
may have also
hurt her reputation.

849
00:39:41,610 --> 00:39:43,339
All right, I'm gonna get back
and brief the department.

850
00:39:43,412 --> 00:39:44,401
Do you want me to drive
you to your car?

851
00:39:44,480 --> 00:39:45,572
No.
Yes.

852
00:39:46,549 --> 00:39:47,641
We'll meet you
back there in a bit.

853
00:39:47,716 --> 00:39:48,808
Okay.

854
00:39:49,451 --> 00:39:50,850
Why are we not getting
the hell out of here?

855
00:39:50,920 --> 00:39:52,615
Because my theory
is half-baked, Gus.

856
00:39:52,755 --> 00:39:54,347
Something isn't
sitting right with me.

857
00:39:54,423 --> 00:39:56,254
You know what's not sitting
right with me, Shawn?

858
00:39:56,325 --> 00:39:58,657
Being stuck in a tiny town
with no phone access

859
00:39:58,727 --> 00:40:00,251
and all white people.
Let's go.

860
00:40:03,799 --> 00:40:04,891
Now where are you going?

861
00:40:09,338 --> 00:40:10,930
If we leave now, I'll
let you play the theme

862
00:40:11,006 --> 00:40:12,974
<i>to Weird Science over and
over in the car. What do you say?</i>

863
00:40:13,042 --> 00:40:15,169
That's happening regardless.
This way.

864
00:40:25,087 --> 00:40:27,920
Here is the most recent
Dual Spires yearbook.

865
00:40:30,859 --> 00:40:32,417
Maudette was
the one emailing us.

866
00:40:32,494 --> 00:40:33,586
That makes no sense.

867
00:40:33,662 --> 00:40:35,630
Why would the killer lure
detectives to the scene

868
00:40:35,698 --> 00:40:36,995
and then start
feeding them clues?

869
00:40:38,100 --> 00:40:40,091
Because she
didn't kill Paula, Gus.

870
00:40:41,437 --> 00:40:42,768
I'm never gonna
leave this town.

871
00:40:42,838 --> 00:40:43,896
She suspected foul play

872
00:40:43,973 --> 00:40:45,167
and knew she'd be
the prime suspect

873
00:40:45,240 --> 00:40:47,435
if anyone found out about her
relationship with Randy.

874
00:40:47,943 --> 00:40:49,308
So she started snooping
around on her own,

875
00:40:49,378 --> 00:40:52,313
discovered the drowning seven
years ago in Santa Barbara.

876
00:40:52,381 --> 00:40:53,814
Found us on the Internet.

877
00:40:53,882 --> 00:40:55,247
So who killed Paula Merral?

878
00:40:55,317 --> 00:40:57,410
I don't know,
but we're gonna find out.

879
00:41:02,858 --> 00:41:03,847
Gus,
stop messing around.

880
00:41:03,926 --> 00:41:05,484
I'm not, Shawn.

881
00:41:08,163 --> 00:41:09,391
Shawn?
Yes, Gus.

882
00:41:09,765 --> 00:41:11,164
Something's burning.

883
00:41:11,400 --> 00:41:12,833
I see that.

884
00:41:14,370 --> 00:41:15,997
Help us!
Somebody help us.

885
00:41:16,071 --> 00:41:18,164
We're stuck
in this tiny room!

886
00:41:18,240 --> 00:41:19,605
Help us!
Let us out!

887
00:41:22,953 --> 00:41:25,012
Shawn, we're gonna die in
this tiny, stupid room.

888
00:41:25,089 --> 00:41:28,149
<i>Gus, don't be the scream
from Holding Back the Years.</i>

889
00:41:28,426 --> 00:41:30,223
You're right, though.
This could be it for us.

890
00:41:30,328 --> 00:41:31,989
Man, we are gonna burn!

891
00:41:32,063 --> 00:41:33,189
I know.

892
00:41:42,273 --> 00:41:43,763
No, wait, wait!
Who are you?

893
00:41:47,778 --> 00:41:48,938
Gus!

894
00:41:59,757 --> 00:42:02,089
Father Westley.
Thank God you were here, literally.

895
00:42:02,160 --> 00:42:04,560
We were about to be Wicker
Men, How did you find us?

896
00:42:04,629 --> 00:42:05,857
I just had faith.

897
00:42:05,930 --> 00:42:07,921
Really?
No, boys.

898
00:42:08,131 --> 00:42:10,827
I just got to town,
I saw the fire,

899
00:42:10,902 --> 00:42:13,462
I saw the tandem bicycle outside.
It all added up.

900
00:42:13,872 --> 00:42:15,840
But how did you know we were
in trouble in the first place?

901
00:42:15,907 --> 00:42:18,205
You hung up on me when I was
transcribing the Latin, Shawn.

902
00:42:18,276 --> 00:42:19,834
I just
I got excited.

903
00:42:19,911 --> 00:42:21,139
I took one little
step to the left.

904
00:42:21,212 --> 00:42:24,909
And that girl, Paula.
She felt she was in danger. She was afraid.

905
00:42:25,250 --> 00:42:27,150
Which led me to be afraid
for the two of you.

906
00:42:27,552 --> 00:42:28,917
And, honestly,
I owed you one anyway

907
00:42:28,987 --> 00:42:30,784
because of that
whole exorcism thing.

908
00:42:31,523 --> 00:42:33,286
What happened to your hair?

909
00:42:33,458 --> 00:42:35,892
Oh. Yeah, it was
an ill-advised attempt

910
00:42:35,960 --> 00:42:38,360
to cover up some gray
that went terribly awry.

911
00:42:39,097 --> 00:42:42,066
But technically,
Sister Rita's to blame.

912
00:42:43,301 --> 00:42:44,700
She's the one
that did my hair.

913
00:42:47,171 --> 00:42:49,162
Guys, get in.
We don't have much time.

914
00:42:49,307 --> 00:42:50,467
You have a car?
What gives?

915
00:42:50,542 --> 00:42:51,702
Why should we trust you?

916
00:42:51,776 --> 00:42:53,141
You probably shouldn't,
but if you stay here

917
00:42:53,211 --> 00:42:54,610
you're gonna be sitting
ducks for whoever it was

918
00:42:54,679 --> 00:42:55,976
that tried to burn
you guys alive.

919
00:42:56,047 --> 00:42:58,072
I'll explain everything
at the cabin. Get in.

920
00:43:13,364 --> 00:43:15,457
Have a seat,
I'll make a fire.

921
00:43:18,036 --> 00:43:20,561
All right, we're listening.

922
00:43:21,039 --> 00:43:24,406
My great grandfather founded Dual Spires.
That's him there.

923
00:43:25,977 --> 00:43:27,342
I might have
guessed that one.

924
00:43:27,579 --> 00:43:29,604
After World War I ended,

925
00:43:29,681 --> 00:43:32,673
he'd seen the
absolute worst in man.

926
00:43:32,784 --> 00:43:34,342
He decided to settle here

927
00:43:34,419 --> 00:43:36,819
with two other soldiers from his
squadron and their families.

928
00:43:36,988 --> 00:43:39,286
<i>I was wrong, it isn't Witness.
 This is The Village.</i>

929
00:43:39,357 --> 00:43:41,416
<i>The Village
was a ridiculous film.</i>

930
00:43:41,492 --> 00:43:44,620
"Those we do not speak of."
Remember all that nonsense?

931
00:43:45,129 --> 00:43:46,790
It's always been
the responsibility

932
00:43:46,864 --> 00:43:48,354
of the three leaders
of the families

933
00:43:48,433 --> 00:43:50,492
to watch over the town
and its best interests.

934
00:43:51,336 --> 00:43:55,204
Try to understand, their
intentions were so pure.

935
00:43:55,707 --> 00:43:58,039
Create a community
that wouldn't be subjected

936
00:43:58,109 --> 00:43:59,770
to the horrors
that they lived through.

937
00:44:01,212 --> 00:44:02,440
And it worked for 40 years.

938
00:44:02,513 --> 00:44:04,879
Dual Spires was perfect,
until...

939
00:44:04,949 --> 00:44:07,474
The great sawmill
fire of '58.

940
00:44:16,494 --> 00:44:17,961
It was arson.

941
00:44:18,563 --> 00:44:20,929
A drifter, who had been
in town doing odd jobs.

942
00:44:21,332 --> 00:44:22,890
Eight people burned to death.

943
00:44:24,135 --> 00:44:26,467
After that,
we became insulated.

944
00:44:27,138 --> 00:44:28,969
Looked at all outsiders
as a threat.

945
00:44:29,040 --> 00:44:31,338
Like Paula.
She was afraid.

946
00:44:31,709 --> 00:44:33,973
She thought she was being watched.
Even followed.

947
00:44:34,278 --> 00:44:35,575
She was.

948
00:44:35,647 --> 00:44:38,343
Which is why Michelle and I were
supportive of her decision to leave.

949
00:44:38,816 --> 00:44:39,976
I...

950
00:44:40,652 --> 00:44:43,212
We loved her so much.

951
00:44:43,788 --> 00:44:45,415
We just wanted her
to be happy.

952
00:44:50,428 --> 00:44:52,726
Did Paula ever know
that you were her father?

953
00:44:56,501 --> 00:44:57,729
Yes.

954
00:44:57,802 --> 00:44:59,235
I had to tell her,
in order to get her

955
00:44:59,303 --> 00:45:00,634
to come here
in the first place.

956
00:45:00,705 --> 00:45:02,263
What about your wife?

957
00:45:02,340 --> 00:45:04,205
Did she know you had
an affair with her sister?

958
00:45:04,676 --> 00:45:05,700
No.

959
00:45:06,010 --> 00:45:07,602
She never will.

960
00:45:07,679 --> 00:45:08,771
I think she's
been through enough.

961
00:45:10,782 --> 00:45:14,183
You know, for a town that prides
itself on honesty and do-goodedness,

962
00:45:14,252 --> 00:45:15,981
you have a lot of skeletons
in your closet.

963
00:45:16,054 --> 00:45:18,318
Judge not, that ye
may be judged, Gus.

964
00:45:19,157 --> 00:45:20,954
Although, I must say,
in this case,

965
00:45:21,526 --> 00:45:23,221
it's pretty messed up.

966
00:45:28,700 --> 00:45:30,327
I know who
killed Paula Merral.

967
00:45:34,505 --> 00:45:35,733
Sheriff, you can
put the gun down.

968
00:45:35,807 --> 00:45:37,934
This is Father Westley.
He saved us.

969
00:45:38,042 --> 00:45:39,771
My hair doesn't normally
look like this.

970
00:45:40,445 --> 00:45:42,037
Bless me father,
for I have sinned.

971
00:45:42,847 --> 00:45:44,781
But I'm afraid
I can't put away this gun.

972
00:45:45,316 --> 00:45:47,284
No, I suppose
you can't.

973
00:45:48,019 --> 00:45:49,281
You see,
the other two families

974
00:45:49,353 --> 00:45:51,412
that settled this town
were the Jacksons

975
00:45:51,956 --> 00:45:54,083
and the Goodens,
am I right?

976
00:45:55,159 --> 00:45:57,992
And as its other two
leaders, you panicked

977
00:45:58,362 --> 00:46:01,126
when you caught wind
that the evil Paula

978
00:46:01,199 --> 00:46:02,791
was running away
with Randy.

979
00:46:03,234 --> 00:46:04,496
I mean,
without the Cinnamon King,

980
00:46:04,569 --> 00:46:07,094
who would lead
over future generations?

981
00:46:07,538 --> 00:46:09,130
The good doctor
can't conceive.

982
00:46:11,242 --> 00:46:13,107
The Barkers didn't have
a child of their own,

983
00:46:13,177 --> 00:46:15,475
which means Randy is
the only direct descendent

984
00:46:15,546 --> 00:46:18,014
to protect Dual Spires
and your way of life.

985
00:46:18,449 --> 00:46:21,850
Especially now that the
sheriff is dying of cancer.

986
00:46:22,186 --> 00:46:25,314
I know he's hurting,
but he won't talk to me.

987
00:46:25,389 --> 00:46:27,789
The two of you wielded
all the power necessary

988
00:46:27,859 --> 00:46:30,191
to kill Paula and make it
look like an accident.

989
00:46:30,828 --> 00:46:32,227
And you would have
gotten away with it too,

990
00:46:32,296 --> 00:46:34,628
if Maudette hadn't
sent those emails.

991
00:46:35,099 --> 00:46:37,966
But even that was nothing a little
rope couldn't take care of.

992
00:46:38,035 --> 00:46:39,195
Isn't that right, sheriff?

993
00:46:39,771 --> 00:46:41,636
You truly are amazing.

994
00:46:42,073 --> 00:46:43,665
But you shouldn't
have come here.

995
00:46:44,275 --> 00:46:45,936
Our business
was not your concern.

996
00:46:46,010 --> 00:46:48,478
Your business is murder.

997
00:46:48,880 --> 00:46:52,680
Her death, though tragic,
saves our future.

998
00:46:53,484 --> 00:46:55,509
You killed my little girl.

999
00:46:57,121 --> 00:46:58,520
What about us?

1000
00:46:58,589 --> 00:47:01,149
Honestly, far less tragic.

1001
00:47:01,926 --> 00:47:03,257
We barely know you.

1002
00:47:03,561 --> 00:47:06,826
I'm in my own special category.
Right?

1003
00:47:07,165 --> 00:47:08,359
Really, father?

1004
00:47:09,667 --> 00:47:12,261
Freeze!
Drop it, now.

1005
00:47:14,005 --> 00:47:14,994
How did you find us?

1006
00:47:15,072 --> 00:47:17,302
Oh, miracles happen
every day, Gus.

1007
00:47:17,508 --> 00:47:18,532
This is a miracle?

1008
00:47:18,609 --> 00:47:21,476
No, I called the detectives
before I came to town.

1009
00:47:21,679 --> 00:47:23,203
You sly old dog.

1010
00:47:24,382 --> 00:47:26,612
We ran into Jack,
and he led us here.

1011
00:47:27,251 --> 00:47:28,878
They thought
this place was a secret.

1012
00:47:29,253 --> 00:47:31,414
I've photographed every
single inch of this town.

1013
00:47:31,489 --> 00:47:32,820
Ah, good work, son.

1014
00:47:33,991 --> 00:47:35,219
